The paper deals with learning a policy for selecting edges in a lazy graph search algorithm for motion planning problems. This involves formulating the problem as a Markov Decision Process (MDP) and using imitation learning to find effective policies. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Systems and Control (cs.SY), or Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
